<!DOCTYPE document PUBLIC "-//APACHE//DTD Documentation V2.0//EN" "http://forrest.apache.org/dtd/document-v20.dtd">
<document>
  <header>
    <title>ESME Clients</title>
  </header>
  <body>
  	<section id="introduction">
		<title>Introduction</title>
		<p>Based on its REST-API, there are a variety of clients available for ESME. These clients are not part of the Apache svn but remain 
		in the Google Code repository. A overview of the possible integration patterns is described <a href="http://blog.esme.us/integration-patterns/">here.</a>
		</p>
		<p>These clients are usual contributed by the community. 
		</p>
		</section>
		<section id="list">
		<title>List of actual clients</title>
		<p>
		<ol>
			<li> <a href="http://code.google.com/p/esmeproject/source/browse/#">ABAP</a></li>
			<li> <a href="http://code.google.com/p/esmeproject/wiki/PureJavascript_messaging_client">Javascript</a></li>
			<li> <a href="http://code.google.com/p/esmeproject/wiki/PL_SQL_Client_for_ESME">PL/SQL</a></li>
			<li> <a href="http://code.google.com/p/esmeproject/source/browse/#">Java</a> for which there is also a client implementation for a SAP NetWeaver implementation </li>
			<li> <a href="http://blog.esme.us/2008/09/27/esme-and-shadow-it-the-vba-client/">VBA</a></li>
			</ol>
		</p> 
		</section>
  </body>
</document>
